{"TopicId":215576,"ForumId":126,"TopicTitle":"TR 4 Rover Wheels - no oomph. (Aside from putting a rocket engine parallel to the ground... how do we go up hill?)","CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T23:03:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T23:03:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot a Rover on Eve.\u00A0 It\u0027s in a \u0027bowl\u0027 of hills.\u00A0 Can\u0027t climb even half way out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know Eve has considerable gravity... but how will resource management - or even basic exploration work if we can\u0027t drive around?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be I\u0027m doing it wrong... but is there any way to get a rover moving other than with sideways Rocket POWAH?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T18:43:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor anyone interested - I \u0027solved\u0027 this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTR-4 REQUIRES a rocket or jet to climb.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022?/topic/215582-rumor-adding-lots-of-tr-4-wheels-will-allow-a-rover-to-climb-hills/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=4262538\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ELink \u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T21:18:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried turning off Auto Friction Control in the parts manager and moving the Friction Level slider way over?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacke","CreatedById":103694,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T23:04:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262845\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679337803\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor anyone interested - I \u0027solved\u0027 this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTR-4 REQUIRES a rocket or jet to climb.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022?/topic/215582-rumor-adding-lots-of-tr-4-wheels-will-allow-a-rover-to-climb-hills/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=4262538\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ELink \u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is a very Kerbal solution to game bugs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-21T18:24:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679347085\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried turning off Auto Friction Control in the parts manager and moving the Friction Level slider way over?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI loaded up my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E save - messed around with Friction control and Traction Control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither worked.\u00A0 TR-4s just got no \u0027oomph\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(OTOH - turning Friction all the way down let me skate to the middle of the depression I was in!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}